olive oil
1 packet basmati rice
1 carrot
1 packet Asian Greens
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 packet sriracha
1 packet Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
drizzle sesame oil

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes. Drain and return to saucepan.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice carrot into rounds. Roughly chop Asian greens.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches until browned and cooked
through, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

• Wipe out the frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook carrot until tender, 3-4 minutes. Add Asian greens and cook until just wilted, 1-2 minutes.
• Return cooked beef to the pan, then add sweet soy seasoning and cook for 1-2 minutes.
• Add Korean stir-fry sauce and sriracha, toss to combine and remove pan from heat.
• While veggies are cooking, in a large bowl, add slaw mix, mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar and sesame oil. Toss to combine. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the sauce is too dry.

• Divide rapid rice between bowls.
• Spoon over Korean sriracha beef and veggies. Serve with creamy
slaw. Enjoy!